        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:22AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 621 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ellendale, or over Bartlett, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lenow, Yum Yum, Barretville, Stanton, Belmont, Ellendale, Woodstock,
Redwood, Rosemark, Hickory Withe, Millington, Arlington, Meux Corner,
Elmore Park, Brunswick, Raleigh, Canaan Grove, Eads, Longtown, and
Moorman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
